= Manually Set ExtentsHint =
#context: lop

"""Manually sets the extentsHint on a USD primitive from a variety of sources."""

== Overview ==

Manually Set ExtentsHint writes `extentsHint` metadata to a USD primitive from one of four sources: a manual min/max value, a SOP node, a geometry file, or a VDB file.

When __Time Dependent__ is enabled, the node evaluates the source each frame and writes time-sampled `extentsHint` values across the specified frame range.

@parameters

Prim Path:
    #id: prim_path
    The USD primitive to set `extentsHint` on.

Time Dependent:
    #id: time_dependent
    When enabled, fetches bounds data per-frame and writes time samples.

Start/End:
    #id: frame_range
    Frame range for time-dependent evaluation.

== Manually ==

Min:
    #id: min
    Minimum bound value (XYZ).

Max:
    #id: max
    Maximum bound value (XYZ).

== From SOP ==

Sop Path:
    #id: sop_path
    Path to a SOP node. Bounds are computed from the SOP geometry.

Type:
    #id: sop_type
    Group type to use when computing bounds.

Group:
    #id: sop_group
    Group name to restrict bounds computation. Leave blank for all geometry.

== From Files ==

Files:
    #id: files
    Geometry file path. When __Time Dependent__ is enabled, evaluated per frame.

Type:
    #id: file_type
    Group type for bounds computation.

Group:
    #id: file_group
    Group name. Leave blank for all.

== From VDB Files ==

VDB Files:
    #id: vdb_files
    VDB file path. When __Time Dependent__ is enabled, evaluated per frame.
